PREP: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. CLEAN: Wash hands. In medium bowl, blend melted butter, hot pepper sauce and vinegar. On plate, blend cornmeal, cayenne and salt. Add chicken to butter mixture; toss to coat evenly. Dip chicken in cornmeal to coat. CLEAN: Wash hands. COOK: Place coated chicken on baking sheet. Bake at 400 degrees F 9 to 11 minutes or until internal juices run clear. (Or insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 170 degrees F.) SERVE: Serve with dressing, assorted fruit and bakery rolls, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.